  <!-- Schools -->
  <section style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #3D5A3E; margin-bottom: 12px;">Knutsford schools</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What schools serve the Knutsford area?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Knutsford Academy is the town's main state secondary, rated Good by Ofsted (November 2021). The academy serves WA16 as its primary catchment - the town has no in-district grammar equivalent, though Altrincham Grammar and The King's School Macclesfield are accessible for independent prep pupils.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">At primary level, Egerton Primary School (Bexton Road) covers the Bexton neighbourhood and the south of town. Buyers in WA16 9 should verify their address falls within this catchment, as Cheshire East Council sets boundaries annually. Manor Park School & Nursery serves the northern side including the Longridge estate. The Ryleys School in Alderley Edge (4 miles) runs independent prep for ages 1-11, preparing pupils for grammar school entrance exams.</p>

