  <!-- Safety -->
  <section style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #3D5A3E; margin-bottom: 12px;">Knutsford crime and safety</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Is Knutsford safe?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Knutsford's crime rate fell 7.1% year-on-year to 47.2 per 1,000 residents, ranking second lowest in the Cheshire East borough behind rural wards south of the M56 (SCOS, 2025).</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Cheshire East as a whole records 62.3 crimes per 1,000 residents - 29% below the England and Wales rate of 88.1 per 1,000 (ONS Crime Survey for England and Wales, year ending March 2024). Knutsford's rate of 47.2 sits below both the borough average and the Golden Triangle neighbour Wilmslow (51.4 per 1,000). Cheshire Constabulary operates a Knutsford local policing unit covering the town and surrounding villages (police.uk, Cheshire Constabulary, 2025).</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Brine Subsidence -->
  <section style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #C4933F; margin-bottom: 12px;">Knutsford buyer alert</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What is brine subsidence risk in Knutsford?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Knutsford sits within the Cheshire Brine Compensation District, one of seven statutory Consultation Areas created by centuries of salt extraction beneath the Cheshire Plain. Historical brine pumping left underground voids that can cause ground movement. Under the Cheshire Brine Subsidence Compensation Acts (1952 and 1964), the Cheshire Brine Subsidence Compensation Board (CBSCB) must be consulted for any new building work in these areas (CBSCB).</p>
      <h3 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 32px 0 12px 0;">What should Knutsford buyers do about brine subsidence during conveyancing?</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Knutsford buyers purchasing in WA16 should commission a salt search as part of their conveyancing process. This search, costing approximately £30-50, reveals whether the property sits within a known subsidence area. The CBSCB typically recommends strengthened foundation designs - raft or jack point foundations - for new builds and extensions. Existing properties with standard foundations are not automatically at risk, but the search confirms the ground conditions relevant to the specific plot.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Brine subsidence is not unique to Knutsford - Northwich, Middlewich, and Winsford share the same extraction history across the Cheshire Plain. Knutsford's property market has absorbed this geological reality for decades and values are not suppressed by it, as the £606,876 average demonstrates.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">A Level 3 RICS Building Survey is the appropriate choice for pre-1960 Knutsford properties, assessing structural integrity relative to ground conditions. A Level 2 HomeBuyer Report does not carry the same investigative depth. The <a href="/buying-guide/survey-types-cheshire" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">Knutsford and Cheshire survey types guide</a> covers survey costs and methodology.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">The salt search and appropriate survey together form the complete due diligence picture for WA16 buyers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Heritage & Lifestyle -->
  <section style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
