        <h4 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 8px 0;">What is brine subsidence risk in Knutsford and how does it affect conveyancing?</h4>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: #333333; margin: 0 0 8px 0;">
          Knutsford sits within the Cheshire salt field, a geological zone where historical brine extraction from underground salt deposits has caused subsidence in parts of the county. Knutsford's direct brine risk is lower than Northwich or Middlewich - the historic brine pumping centres - but the town sits within the British Geological Survey's salt dissolution zone. Knutsford conveyancing requires a CON29M mining search (approximately £30-£50) to confirm whether a specific property falls within a Cheshire Brine Subsidence Compensation Board claim area.
        </p>
